# CI/CD Pipeline Walkthrough

I have created the necessary files to deploy your AWS Lambda function using a CI/CD pipeline (AWS CodePipeline + CodeBuild) with AWS SAM.

## Files Created

### 1. Lambda Function
[lambda_function.py](file:///c%3A/Users/tejaswini.v/OneDrive%20-%20Idexcel/Documents/CI-CD%20pipeline/lambda_function.py)
- A simple Python function that returns a "Hello from AWS Lambda CI/CD Pipeline!" message.

### 2. Infrastructure as Code (SAM Template)
[template.yaml](file:///c%3A/Users/tejaswini.v/OneDrive%20-%20Idexcel/Documents/CI-CD%20pipeline/template.yaml)
- Defines the Lambda function resource (`MyCiCdFunction`).
- Sets the runtime to `python3.9`.
- Uses the [lambda_function.py](file:///c:/Users/tejaswini.v/OneDrive%20-%20Idexcel/Documents/CI-CD%20pipeline/lambda_function.py) code from the current directory.

### 3. Build Specification
[buildspec.yml](file:///c%3A/Users/tejaswini.v/OneDrive%20-%20Idexcel/Documents/CI-CD%20pipeline/buildspec.yml)
- Installs dependencies (if any).
- Builds the SAM application (`sam build`).
- Deploys the application (`sam deploy`).
    - **Note**: The deploy command is configured to create/update a stack named `my-cicd-lambda-stack`.

### 4. Documentation
[README.md](file:///c%3A/Users/tejaswini.v/OneDrive%20-%20Idexcel/Documents/CI-CD%20pipeline/README.md)
- Instructions on how to set up the repository and trigger the build.

## Next Steps for You

1. **Commit and Push**: Push these files to your source repository (AWS CodeCommit, GitHub, etc.).
2. **Setup CodeBuild/CodePipeline**:
    - Create a new Project in AWS CodeBuild pointing to your repository.
    - Use the [buildspec.yml](file:///c:/Users/tejaswini.v/OneDrive%20-%20Idexcel/Documents/CI-CD%20pipeline/buildspec.yml) file I created.
    - Ensure your CodeBuild Service Role has permissions to create CloudFormation stacks, Lambda functions, and IAM roles.
3. **Run Build**: Trigger the build and watch your Lambda function get deployed!
